  "title": "Core Concepts of Foundations of Introduction to Java",
  "lessonText": "This lesson introduces the foundational concepts of Java programming.",
  "data": {
    "content": "Java is a versatile programming language used for various applications.\n\n- **Object-Oriented**: Java is built on the principles of object-oriented programming, which promotes code reusability and organization.\n- **Platform Independence**: Java code can run on any device that has the Java Virtual Machine (JVM) installed.\n- **Syntax**: Java syntax is similar to C++ and is designed to be easy to read and write.\n- **Data Types**: Java has two categories of data types: primitive (int, char, etc.) and reference (objects).\n- **Control Structures**: Java supports various control structures like loops (for, while) and conditionals (if, switch) to control the flow of execution."
  }
}
